&lt;h1&gt;Volunteer Minibus Driver&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a voluntary minibus driver to transport patients to appointments/therapy groups, day trips to the coast, and various other places of interest. It is essential for drivers to have a clean driving licence be patient and have caring and have a sympathetic nature. Out of pocket travel expenses will be paid. Applicants must ideally live within a 5 mile radius of location of the Memorial Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Volunteers are valued members of the Trust making a difference in many areas by supporting patients and staff in various ways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel that you are able to support us and you wish to do something positive to becoming a volunteer, please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Langford, Voluntary Services Co-Ordinator: julie.langford@nhs.net/ 020 88368510/1&lt;/p&gt;
